                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.148,
                                "byte_start": 89042,
                                "byte_stop": 125718,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has the opinion in 04-433, Anza versus Ideal Steel Supply Corporation."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.148,
                        "stop": 315.716,
                        "byte_start": 125718,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.148,
                                "stop": 19.197,
                                "byte_start": 125718,
                                "byte_stop": 165842,
                                "text": "In this case, two steel supply companies, Ideal Steel Supply and National Steel Supply, compete with each other in the New York City area."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.197,
                                "stop": 26.378,
                                "byte_start": 165842,
                                "byte_stop": 194577,
                                "text": "They each operate one store in Queens and they each operate one store in the Bronx, and the competing stores are nearby each other."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.378,
                                "stop": 30.111,
                                "byte_start": 194577,
                                "byte_stop": 209519,
                                "text": "Ideal sued National and National\u2019s owners."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 30.111,
                                "stop": 42.279,
                                "byte_start": 209519,
                                "byte_stop": 258211,
                                "text": "Ideal claimed that National and its owners, Joseph and Vincent Anza, failed to charge cash-paying customers for New York sales tax and that they then failed to report the cash sales to the state tax authorities."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.279,
                                "stop": 47.811,
                                "byte_start": 258211,
                                "byte_stop": 280363,
                                "text": "Ideal says that these actions gave National a competitive advantage in attracting customers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.811,
                                "stop": 54.981,
                                "byte_start": 280363,
                                "byte_stop": 308993,
                                "text": "Ideal sued, alleging a violation of the Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act, commonly known as RICO."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.981,
                                "stop": 65.508,
                                "byte_start": 308993,
                                "byte_stop": 351102,
                                "text": "It claimed that the Anzas violated Section 1962(c) of the Act by conducting National\u2019s affairs through a pattern of defrauding the State of New York."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.508,
                                "stop": 75.527,
                                "byte_start": 351102,
                                "byte_stop": 391226,
                                "text": "It also claimed the Anzas and National violated 1962(a) of the Act by investing the proceeds of their scheme in the establishment of National\u2019s Bronx store."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.527,
                                "stop": 82.419,
                                "byte_start": 391226,
                                "byte_stop": 418812,
                                "text": "National and the Anzas moved to dismiss Ideal\u2019s complaint, and the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York granted the motion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.419,
                                "stop": 87.775,
                                "byte_start": 418812,
                                "byte_stop": 440232,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the 2nd Circuit reversed, concluding that Ideal could maintain these claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.775,
                                "stop": 94.23,
                                "byte_start": 440232,
                                "byte_stop": 466041,
                                "text": "We now reverse the Court of Appeals\u2019 judgments with respect to Ideal\u2019s claim based on Section 1962(c)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.23,
                                "stop": 106.48,
                                "byte_start": 466041,
                                "byte_stop": 515047,
                                "text": "In Holmes versus Securities Investors Protection Corporation, this Court held that a plaintiff may sue for a RICO violation only if the violation was the proximate cause of the plaintiff\u2019s injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.48,
                                "stop": 114.869,
                                "byte_start": 515047,
                                "byte_stop": 548588,
                                "text": "Now, critical to the proximate-cause analysis is the directness of the relationship between the asserted violation and the claimed harm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.869,
                                "stop": 128.051,
                                "byte_start": 548588,
                                "byte_stop": 601251,
                                "text": "In this case, Ideal\u2019s theory is that Joseph and Vinson Anza harmed it by defrauding the New York Tax Authority and then used the proceeds of their fraudulent activities to offer lower prices and thereby attract some of Ideal\u2019s customers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.051,
                                "stop": 132.916,
                                "byte_start": 601251,
                                "byte_stop": 620791,
                                "text": "The direct victim of this conduct, though, was the State of New York, not Ideal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 132.916,
                                "stop": 138.507,
                                "byte_start": 620791,
                                "byte_stop": 643151,
                                "text": "Ideal asserts it suffered its own harms when the Anzas failed to charge customers for the applicable sales tax."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.507,
                                "stop": 148.582,
                                "byte_start": 643151,
                                "byte_stop": 683380,
                                "text": "But the cause of these harms is a set of actions, offering lower prices entirely distinct from the alleged RICO violations, which involved defrauding the state."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.582,
                                "stop": 153.776,
                                "byte_start": 683380,
                                "byte_stop": 704173,
                                "text": "Ideal\u2019s claim thus could not satisfy the requirement of proximate causation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.776,
                                "stop": 158.364,
                                "byte_start": 704173,
                                "byte_stop": 722564,
                                "text": "This result is confirmed by considering how the directness requirement works."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.364,
                                "stop": 167.41,
                                "byte_start": 722564,
                                "byte_stop": 758717,
                                "text": "One aspect of it is designed to recognize the difficulty that can arise when a court attempts to ascertain damages caused by some remote action."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.41,
                                "stop": 172.921,
                                "byte_start": 758717,
                                "byte_stop": 780764,
                                "text": "Here, National could have lowered its prices for any number of reasons unconnected to the asserted tax frauds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.921,
                                "stop": 177.996,
                                "byte_start": 780764,
                                "byte_stop": 801035,
                                "text": "Likewise, the fact that a company commits tax fraud does not mean that company will lower its prices."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.996,
                                "stop": 184.203,
                                "byte_start": 801035,
                                "byte_stop": 825904,
                                "text": "The additional cash could go anywhere, from asset acquisition to research and development to dividend payouts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.203,
                                "stop": 191.006,
                                "byte_start": 825904,
                                "byte_stop": 853071,
                                "text": "There is, in addition, a second discontinuity between the RICO violation and the asserted injury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.006,
                                "stop": 196.682,
                                "byte_start": 853071,
                                "byte_stop": 875850,
                                "text": "Ideal\u2019s lost sales could have resulted from factors other than the petitioners\u2019 alleged tax frauds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 196.682,
                                "stop": 208.119,
                                "byte_start": 875850,
                                "byte_stop": 921617,
                                "text": "Businesses lose and gain customers for many reasons; it would require a complex assessment to determine what portion of Ideal\u2019s lost sales were the product of National\u2019s decreased prices."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 208.119,
                                "stop": 212.862,
                                "byte_start": 921617,
                                "byte_stop": 940529,
                                "text": "Undertaking such inquiries is inconsistent with our opinion in Holmes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 212.862,
                                "stop": 231.291,
                                "byte_start": 940529,
                                "byte_stop": 1014299,
                                "text": "The requirement of a direct causal connection is especially warranted where the immediate victims of an alleged RICO violation can be expected to vindicate the laws by pursuing their own claims, and here Ideal accuses the Anzas of defrauding the State of New York out of a substantial sum of money."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.291,
                                "stop": 236.237,
                                "byte_start": 1014299,
                                "byte_stop": 1034048,
                                "text": "If those allegations are true, the State of New York can be expected to pursue appropriate remedies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.237,
                                "stop": 244.707,
                                "byte_start": 1034048,
                                "byte_stop": 1067902,
                                "text": "In sum, we hold that Ideal\u2019s claim based on Section 1962(c) does not meet the requirement of proximate causation discussed in Holmes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.707,
                                "stop": 251.619,
                                "byte_start": 1067902,
                                "byte_stop": 1095592,
                                "text": "Ideal also asserts a claim based on a violation of Section 1962(a) dealing with the investment of racketeering proceeds."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.619,
                                "stop": 261.006,
                                "byte_start": 1095592,
                                "byte_stop": 1133104,
                                "text": "National and the Anzas say the proximate-cause analysis should function identically for purposes of Ideal\u2019s 1962 claim and its Section 1962(a) claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 261.006,
                                "stop": 269.359,
                                "byte_start": 1133104,
                                "byte_stop": 1166541,
                                "text": "The proximate-cause inquiry, however, requires careful consideration of the relationship between the injury asserted and the injurious conduct alleged."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 269.359,
                                "stop": 282.329,
                                "byte_start": 1166541,
                                "byte_stop": 1218368,
                                "text": "Because Section 1962(c) and Section 1962(a) articulate distinct prohibitions, it is at least debatable whether Ideal\u2019s two claims should be analyzed in an identical fashion for proximate-cause purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 282.329,
                                "stop": 288.615,
                                "byte_start": 1218368,
                                "byte_stop": 1243550,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals held that Ideal adequately pleaded its Section 1962(a) claim, but the court did not addressed proximate causation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 288.615,
                                "stop": 299.618,
                                "byte_start": 1243550,
                                "byte_stop": 1287540,
                                "text": "We decline to consider the claim without the benefit of the Court of Appeals\u2019 analysis, particularly when the parties devoted nearly all of their attention in this Court to the Section 1962(c) claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 299.618,
                                "stop": 315.716,
                                "byte_start": 1287540,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We therefore vacate the Court of Appeals\u2019 judgment with respect to Ideal\u2019s Section 1962(a) claim; Justice Scalia has issued a concurring opinion; Justice Thomas has issued an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part; Justice Breyer has issued an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
